Using CSS only (without adding additional HTML attributes), style articles so that they occupy the whole browser window and have the following properties:


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <title>Articles</title>
  <style>
    /* Write your CSS solution here (do not edit the surrounding HTML) */
    article:nth-child(1){
      background-color: red;
      position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; right: 50%; bottom: 50%;
    }
    article:nth-child(2){
      background-color: yellow;
      position: absolute; top: 0; left: 50%; right: 0; bottom: 50%;
    }
    article:nth-child(3){
      background-color: blue;
      position: absolute; top: 50%; left: 0; right: 50%; bottom: 0;
    }
    article:nth-child(4){
      background-color: green;
      position: absolute; top: 50%; left: 50%; right: 0; bottom: 0;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <article>First</article>
  <article>Second</article>
  <article>Third</article>
  <article>Fourth</article>
</body>
</html>
